<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUN 94 / Foreign investment in Mexico increases by 42.7%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MEXICO CITY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Foreign investment in Mexico reached Dollars 6.45bn in the first five months
of the year, an increase of 42.7 per cent over the same period a year
earlier, according to the Trade Ministry, Reuter reports from Mexico City.
The figure took total investment during the administration of President
Carlos Salinas de Gortari to Dollars 48.19bn - or twice the target for the
six-year term of Dollars 24bn.
