<HEADLINE>
FT  28 JUN 94 / World Cup '94: Greek fans uncompromising
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Greece has been stunned by its team's second consecutive World Cup loss,
suffered when Bulgaria trounced the Greek side 4-0.
'Greek national team shame on you,' the Athens afternoon daily Ta Nea said
in a banner headline, accompanied by a half-page picture showing fans at an
Athens coffee shop making obscene gestures at a TV set.
Other papers, television and radio were much more harsh in their criticism
of the team and its coach, Alketas Panagoulias.
'The people are enraged,' the daily Eleftheros Typos said.
