<HEADLINE>
FT  27 JUN 94 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The order of currencies in the EMS grid was unchanged in spite of bond
market volatility that caused a flight of investors to the safe haven
D-Mark. In a week during which trading was dominated by dollar turbulence,
the spread between the weakest and strongest currencies narrowed to just
over 5 per cent from nearly 6 per cent a week ago.
Currencies, Page 29
