</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Women may have to wait until the year 2025 before they earn the same pay as
men, says a report today from the Labour Research Department, a union-funded
body.
In 1970, before the first Equal Pay Act, women earned 63 per cent of men's
hourly pay. The proportion increased to 79 per cent last year.
